</div></div><div class="mods-column-ll"><div class="whitebox"><h2>BEGINNING TURFSIDE</h2>After you've read our <a href="http://fav.me/dbj86wg">Code of Conduct</a>&nbsp;and officially joined Turfside, you will be gifted 50,000c and one Adult stall.&nbsp;Once you see your Username in the Spreadsheet (Banking&gt;"The Vault"), you can begin playing!

While you are welcome to jump right in, there are a few thing you should know first! Don't let the length of the journal scare you, Turfside is very intuitive once you've gotten started. Please read this guide and the linked information carefully. If you have any questions, feel free to ask in the Discord server! We'd be happy to help!</div></div></div>
<h1>PLAYER LIMITS and REFRESH</h1><div class="whitebox">Turfside runs on a weekly schedule. Each player is limited in the number of Trainings, Races and Leases they can do each week. The exact maximum limit depends on the type of Trainer hired, the type of Jockey hired, Backstretch pass bonuses (if purchased), and the player's PR Bonuses.&nbsp;

Once you have reached your weekly limit, you will be unable to submit more until the "refresh". Each week, this <b>refresh occurs on Sunday at 11:59 PM CST</b>. Please keep in mind that the refresh is performed manually by staff, so occasionally it may run a little late and we thank you for your patience! After the refresh, every player's limits are reset so they can submit again. A countdown can be found on :devturfside:'s page on the top right.&nbsp;
</div><div align="center"><small><a href="https://sta.sh/01x1msyutfnh#top">Back to Top</a></small></div>

<h1>CURRENCY SYSTEM and REFERRALS</h1><div class="left"><div class="whitebox">You may have noticed when you joined, you were gifted 50,000 Coins!&nbsp;This fictional currency is the <i>only</i> form of currency approved for essential group elements (horses, slots, items). 

<b>You may <u>NOT</u> sell or buy horses/slots/etc for dA points, real currency, or any other form of fictional currency</b>. Only coins. Extra elements that <i>don't</i> impact game-play, such as Stable Maps, YHHs, etc., may be bought with any type of currency. 

A player's up-to-date coin balance is recorded in The Vault.&nbsp;You can earn coins by racing, offering horses up for breedings, selling horses and unused items, referrals, advertising the group, leasing other players' horses for a fee, and so on.&nbsp;</div></div><div class="right"><div class="purplebox"><h3>Referrals and Advertising</h3><b>Each time a player lists you as their referrer upon joining, you'll be eligible to earn 10,000c Coins.</b> There is no limit on referrals! However, the new player must obtain their first horse (via any method) and hire a Trainer and Jockey before your account will be credited.

<b>Additionally, advertising Turfside</b> in a Poll, Journal,&nbsp; Status, Art submission (with the description advertising TS), or comment (discord or dA) will earn you 5,000c. This can be done <b>once per month. </b>Note the group with proof to redeem. A r<u>equirement</u>&nbsp;is that you must mention a feature of Turfside you like the most in your advertisement and link to the group.</div></div><div class="clear"></div><div align="center"><small><a href="https://sta.sh/01x1msyutfnh#top">Back to Top</a></small></div>

<h1>TRAINER INFORMATION</h1><div class="whitebox">In Turfside, horses have <b>5 different stats</b> (Speed, Stamina, Breaking, Power, Courage) that helps determine how successful they'll be in races. In order to increase a horse's stats, you must first<a href="https://www.deviantart.com/comments/1/798609698/4735584820"> hire a Trainer</a>. Once hired, the fee will be deducted from your Vault and the Trainer will work for you for one IRL month. Your trainer's "expiration date" will be listed in The Vault under column "TED".&nbsp; Your "TU" shows how many trainings you have available.</div><div class="hh"><div class="ll"><div class="purplebox">There are four different Trainers types, the more expensive, the more you can train your own horses and lease others' horses!</div>
<div class="divTableBody"><div class="divTableRow">
<div class="divTableHead"><h4>TYPE</h4></div>
<div class="divTableHead"><h4>FEE</h4></div>
<div class="divTableHead"><h4>BENEFITS</h4></div>
</div><div class="divTableRow">
<div class="divTableCell">Rookie Trainer</div>
<div class="divTableCell">2,000c / 1 month</div>
<div class="divTableCell">Train horses 20x Week&nbsp; Lease 20x Week</div></div><div class="divTableRow">
<div class="divTableCell">Rising Star Trainer</div>
<div class="divTableCell">6,000c / 1 month</div>
<div class="divTableCell">Train horses 30x Week Lease 30x Week
</div></div><div class="divTableRow">
<div class="divTableCell">All- Star Trainer</div>
<div class="divTableCell">12,000c / 1 month</div>
<div class="divTableCell">Train horses 50x Week&nbsp; Lease 50x Week
</div>
</div></div><div class="divTableRow">
<div class="divTableCell">Hall of Fame Trainer</div>
<div class="divTableCell">24,000c / 1 month</div>
<div class="divTableCell">Train horses 80x Week&nbsp; Lease horses 80x Week
</div></div></div><div class="rr"><div class="whitebox">When a trainer's contract expires, you may choose to rehire them or select a different trainer type. You may also fire a trainer before the one month contract is finished.

For example, if you previously had a Rookie Trainer and you fire him and hire an All-Star Trainer, your weekly Training and Leasing limits will jump from 20 to 50 the moment the new trainer is hired. 

This is the same when downgrading Trainers. If you had an All-Star Trainer hired and you fire him to hire a Rookie Trainer, your training and leasing limit drops immediately from 50 to 20. 

<b>If this causes you to be over your limit</b>, then you won't be able to train until the refresh and your TU is reset.</div></div>
