<h1>JOCKEY INFORMATION</h1><div class="whitebox">Racing allows players to earn coins, PR Bonuses, and rise on the leader board! But first, you must <a href="https://www.deviantart.com/comments/1/798610705/4735586122">hire a Jockey</a> in order to race. Jockeys now require an up-front fee and will work for you for one month like a Trainer. When you hire a Jockey, it'll be listed under "Jockey Type" in The Vault and their expiration date will be listed under "JED." When a jockey's contract expires, you won't be able to race until you hire another one.&nbsp; Your "RU" shows how many races you have available.</div><div class="hh"><div class="ll"><div class="purplebox">There are four different Jockey types, the more expensive their fee, the more often you can race your horses!</div>
<div class="divTableBody"><div class="divTableRow">
