<h1>OBTAINING and RETIRING HORSES</h1><div class="left"><div class="whitebox"><h3>OBTAINING HORSES</h3>Now that we've covered the basics and you've received your gift of one free Adult stall, you're ready for your first horse! Players can obtain horses through buying custom imports, buying horses from other players, winning a bid on a horse at the Auction House, as prizes, and by breeding two horses together to create a foal. 

<b>Players with less than three horses get a discount on Customs</b>, so it is recommended for new players go there for their first horse. Remember that in the future you will need to purchase a stall <i>before</i> getting additional horses!</div></div><div class="right"><div class="whitebox"><h3>"RETIRING" / DECEASING YOUR HORSE</h3>As mentioned, a player can have a maximum of 15 adult stalls, which means you can only house 15 horses at a time. Eventually, it may be necessary to get rid of horses to make space for new ones. Players can sell their horses to other stables, go through the "Buy Back" program, or simply "retire" their horses. 

Retirement is an irreversible action which removes the horse from your stable so they can no longer be trained, raced, or sold, nor can new slot bookings be made. There is no item to bring back a retired horse, so be confident in your decision. <b>To retire, please note the group with the horse's name and ID!</b></div></div><div class="clear"></div><div align="center"><small><a href="https://sta.sh/01x1msyutfnh#top">Back to Top</a></small></div>

